The [[Kraken]] is a [[Boss#Slayer_bosses|Slayer boss]] and can therefore only be killed while on a [[Slayer task]] to kill it, or ([[Cave kraken|cave]]) kraken. The Kraken is located in the [[Kraken Cove]].

It is recommended to use the [[Magic]] attack style to fight the Kraken, as [[Ranged]] deals 1/7th of its normal damage{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1699360516488011950|date=6 September 2023|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/107527|archivedate=6 September 2023|quote=If you rolled 0 damage, it stays as 0. If you rolled >=1 damage, it's divided by 7, with a floor of 1. Accuracy is not affected.}} and it is immune to [[Melee]], due to the fact that it cannot be reached by Melee attacks. As there are no complex mechanics, the Kraken is a popular [[boss]] (therefore it may be hard to find an empty world). Players can alternatively create an [[instance]] for {{Coins|25,000}} coins, which lasts until the player leaves or logs out.

==Requirements==
*Level {{SCP|Slayer|87}} and a [[Cave kraken]] task (requiring {{SCP|Magic|50}})

== Suggested skills ==

* {{SCP|Magic|75+}}
* {{SCP|Defence|70+}}
* {{SCP|Hitpoints|75+}}

==Transportation==
The Kraken is located in a separated section of the [[Kraken Cove]]. The quickest way to get to this dungeon is via [[fairy rings]]:
*Use the code {{Fairycode|AKQ}}, then run west to the dungeon entrance.

Run west after entering the Kraken cove to find the entrance to the Kraken's lair.

==Mechanics==
===Releasing the Kraken===
[[File:Kraken fight.png|thumb|300px|Without a fishing explosive, players must disturb the four smaller whirlpools before they can successfully release the Kraken.]]
To disturb the Kraken and start the fight, a [[fishing explosive]] should be used on the large whirlpool, which will cause the Kraken and all four tentacles to emerge and attack at once. A fishing explosive only costs 60 [[coins]] and can be easily bought from any slayer master. Without this, the player must first disturb the smaller whirlpools, which will each spawn an [[Enormous Tentacle]]. The tentacles can be killed, but this is ill-advised as they have high hitpoints and are unaffected by slayer task bonuses. Once all four small whirlpools are disturbed, the player can then disturb the larger whirlpool, which will cause the Kraken to emerge and attack; disturbing the larger whirlpool without disturbing all four smaller ones will not produce a response. A ranged weapon with a range of 7 or more tiles is needed to reach the back two whirlpools from the bridge without having to move.

During the fight, it is best to focus on the Kraken and tank the hits from the smaller tentacles. The Kraken is very unlikely to kill the player unless they are extremely unlucky, as its attack has such poor accuracy despite having a high max hit, even in magic robes. It is still best to stay above 45 hitpoints to avoid the risk of getting killed.

===Attack styles===
During the fight, the player will be attacked by four [[Enormous Tentacle]]s and by the [[Kraken]] itself:
*The Kraken and the tentacles only attack with a [[typeless]] [[magical ranged]] attack:
**'Typeless' means that [[protection prayers]] will not have any effect.
**'Magical ranged' means that the attack accuracy is decided by the ranged attack bonuses of the Kraken and the magic defence bonuses of the player.
**The max hit of this attack is 28 from Kraken, and 2 from each tentacle.
**The attacks have an attack speed of 4 (i.e. every 2.4 seconds). Kraken's attacks are fairly inaccurate, but the tentacles are relatively accurate.

==Tips==
The Kraken is a popular [[boss]], therefore it may be hard to find an empty world. To combat this, players can create a private [[instance]] for {{Coins|25,000}} coins. 

An advantage of a private instance is that dropped items stay on the ground for a longer period of time. Normally, items disappear after two minutes upon being dropped and other players can see it after one minute. However, this is not an issue if instancing, as dropped items disappear in 3 hours within the [[Kraken Cove]] instance.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1688468997375762432|date=7 August 2023|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/96330|archivedate=10 August 2023|quote=I believe those are 180 mins. This is not universal across all instances, but it's been enabled for quite a few repeatable boss rooms.}} As the [[Kraken]] regularly drops a generous amount of food in the form of 5 [[edible seaweed]] or 5 [[shark]]s, the instance makes it a lot easier on the player to juggle these food sources before they disappear.

Players attempting long trips or the Kraken's stamina-based Combat Achievements (e.g. [[One Hundred Tentacles]]) may benefit from using the [[Sanguinesti staff]], as its passive healing greatly reduces the dependency for food drops.

It is highly recommended to turn Auto Retaliate off when fighting the Kraken, as the tentacles continue to attack the player after it has been killed. With Auto Retaliate off, after a [[fishing explosive]] is used, the player will automatically attack the [[Kraken]] when vulnerable.

When exiting the instance, either by leaving, dying, or logging out, all items on the ground will be permanently lost. If a player dies, all items carried will be moved to a gravestone outside the instance.

==Equipment==
Magic equipment, while providing less defence against the Kraken's attacks, is offset by the damage bonus provided from higher tier sets. It is only recommended to bring magic armour if it is virtus or ancestral; otherwise, use the best ranged armour instead, as the damage bonus provided by other robes is not worth the tradeoff.

